		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Great Pacific Garbage Patch</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:352px;"><a href="/wiki/File:North_Pacific_Gyre_World_Map.png" class="image" title="The Garbage Patch is located within the North Pacific Gyre, one of the five major oceanic gyres."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/64/North_Pacific_Gyre_World_Map.png/350px-North_Pacific_Gyre_World_Map.png" width="350" height="229" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:North_Pacific_Gyre_World_Map.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The Garbage Patch is located within the <a href="/wiki/North_Pacific_Gyre" title="North Pacific Gyre" class="mw-redirect">North Pacific Gyre</a>, one of the five major oceanic <a href="/wiki/Gyre" title="Gyre" class="mw-redirect">gyres</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Great Pacific Garbage Patch</b>, also described as the <b>Eastern Garbage Patch</b> or the <b>Pacific Trash Vortex</b>, is a <a href="/wiki/Gyre" title="Gyre" class="mw-redirect">gyre</a> of <a href="/wiki/Marine_debris" title="Marine debris">marine debris</a> in the central North Pacific Ocean located roughly between <a href="/wiki/135th_meridian_west" title="135th meridian west">135°</a> to <a href="/wiki/155th_meridian_west" title="155th meridian west">155°W</a> and <a href="/wiki/35th_parallel_north" title="35th parallel north">35°</a> to <a href="/wiki/42nd_parallel_north" title="42nd parallel north">42°N</a>. The patch is characterized by exceptionally high concentrations of suspended plastic and other debris that have been trapped by the currents of the <a href="/wiki/North_Pacific_Gyre" title="North Pacific Gyre" class="mw-redirect">North Pacific Gyre</a>.</p>
